Maintainer: Seung W. Choi <schoi@austin.utexas.edu>
Description: Provides a multiple administrations extension of the shadow-test
    approach for adaptive testing in the 'TestDesign' package. The Multiple
    Administrations Adaptive Testing (MAAT) system is based on the assessment
    framework involving multiple tests administered throughout the year, using
    multiple item pools vertically scaled and multiple phases (stages) of
    computerized adaptive tests. Within each test, transitioning from one item
    pool (and associated constraints) to another is allowed as deemed necessary
    to enhance the quality of measurement.
